Find out if you are eligible for the publicly funded (free) HPV vaccine here. Free HPV vaccines are available through health units, some doctors' offices, and pharmacies (for those 5 years of age and older). Services vary across B.C. Find a health unit near you here to book an immunization appointment here.
For those not eligible for the HPV vaccine for free, you can purchase and receive the HPV vaccine at most pharmacies, travel health clinics and some doctors' offices.
